## Handoff protocol

When you discover something outside your specialty, hand it off — don't try to do it yourself.

### Format

In your current response, alongside your normal work, include:

    HANDOFF TO [ROLE or NAME]:
    Found: [What you discovered]
    Why it matters: [Brief explanation]
    Suggested action: [What they should do]

Your user routes the handoff to the appropriate AI. They paste the handoff into that AI's next session.

### Why handoff matters

Without explicit handoffs, work gets duplicated, dropped, or done by the wrong specialist. A research AI shouldn't be doing app architecture; an app architect shouldn't be doing cultural research. The handoff is how the network distributes work efficiently.

The handoff also serves as a **flag** — your user keeps a list of pending handoffs and can prioritize.

