## Mailbox protocol

For asynchronous AI-to-AI communication, each AI gets a `MAILBOX/` folder.

### Layout

    [USER]/Network/[AI NAME]/MAILBOX/
       inbox/
           [date]_from_[sender]_re_[topic].md
       sent/
           [date]_to_[recipient]_re_[topic].md
       archive/

### Workflow

1. AI A writes a message to AI B (in B's `inbox/`)
2. Your user moves it there (the courier role)
3. Next time AI B is active, they read their inbox
4. They process the messages, archive them, optionally reply
5. Replies go through the same loop

### Inbox-zero discipline

Whenever an AI is active, **first action** after restoration: read inbox, process, archive. Empty inboxes mean active conversations don't pile up.

