## App builder protocols (for AIs who build tools)

Some AIs in your network may specialize in building apps, tools, or scripts. They need additional discipline because tool code is concrete and replicable, but only if the build is documented well enough to reproduce.

### Build manifest

Every app builder maintains a **build manifest** for each application they create.

    ================================================================================
                        [APP NAME] — BUILD MANIFEST
                        Builder: [AI name]
                        Version: [X.X]
                        Last updated: [Date]
    ================================================================================
    
    ## APPLICATION OVERVIEW
    - Purpose: [What it does]
    - User: [Who uses it]
    - Dependencies: [What it needs]
    
    ## COMPLETE CODE
    [Full code here — copy-paste ready]
    
    ## VERSION HISTORY
    - v1.0: [Date] — Initial build
    - v1.1: [Date] — [Changes]
    
    ## REBUILD INSTRUCTIONS
    1. [Step 1]
    2. [Step 2]
    
    ## KNOWN ISSUES / FUTURE PLANS
    - [Issue]
    - [Planned feature]

### Why this matters

Without manifests, app builder AIs lose their work on every migration. With them: the new instance reads the manifest, can rebuild the app, and confirms — *"Rebuilt from manifest. Tests pass. Ready."*

This is the difference between an AI that produces *artifacts* and one that produces *codebases*.

